Experiment 2: Working with Gradle: Setting Up a Gradle Project, Understanding Build 
Scripts (Groovy DSL), Dependency Management and Task Automation. 

Step 1: Create a New Gradle Project 

1. Create a new directory for your project and navigate to it: 

1. mkdir Groovy

2. cd Groovy 

2. Run the Gradle init command:  

      3.   gradle init --type java-application

Step 2: Explore the Project Structure


A. Groovy DSL Example (build.gradle)  
Below is an example of a basic build.gradle for a Java application using Groovy DSL: 

➢ gedit build.gradle 

4. Run the Custom Task:  
• Command:  

➢ gradle hello 

• Expected Output:  
You should see:  
> Task :hello  
Hello, Gradle!

Task Dependencies: (change the task name and run)
Command: 

➢ gradle greet

5. Running and Verifying Your Gradle Project:

gradle build 
